definitions.definition: A staff with a hooked end similar to a shepherd 's crook , or with a cross at the end, carried by an abbot , bishop , or archbishop as a symbol of office.
A young fern frond , before it has unrolled ; fiddlehead

main_definition: A staff with a hooked end similar to a shepherd 's crook , or with a cross at the end, carried by an abbot , bishop , or archbishop as a symbol of office.
secondary_definitions: ( botany ) A young fern frond , before it has unrolled ; fiddlehead
